All right, now you want to describe some work that you've done. And the first thing you want to start with is what problem did you solve?

So why start with the problem? Well, because at the end of the day it's the problem that matters. People are listening to you talk. And what's kind of going through their head is, who cares? Why am I listening to this? Why should I care? And that problem is the answer.
0:42
Who cares? It's who cares about that problem being solved. So if you don't make the problem clear, nobody's going to care.

